HEADWORD: Euripus
<hw>Eu*ri"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/;
<grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ a rushing motion.]</ety> <def>A strait; a
narrow tract of water, where the tide, or a current, flows and reflows
with violence, as the ancient frith of this name between Eub⟦oe⟧a and
B⟦oe⟧otia. Hence, a flux and reflux.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
